originalText.text: I  came in to get my hair in short weave What I received was a glued on weave that sat on my head looking like a toupee! Within a week it loosened up. The weave I received cost me $160 which was a short bob. Never again! That didn't even include the weaving hair. If u think about going there your better going to the African hairbraidning spot! At least you get quality hair do. Smdh....

originalText.text: 1 demand you to read this before you go there! last time i went here for my bday and i regret it!! the place was messy. when she took me to wash my hair, she dropped water all over my clothes and blamed me. water was dripping down my back and it was not good. then we went to press it and while she was doing it, i think she heard me say 'ow' several times but ignored it. while she was doing it it hurt really bad because my hair was so dry i can hear my hair breaking and it wasn't good my hair did turn out good but the process was sooooooooooo awful i will never come here again!!!!!!!!! Update: my hair ended up being damaged after this. It had to take me 2 years to get my curls back after I literally told her to use heat protector I will never get over how horrible my experience was.
